[Student "S"]
{EAST has a powerful hand (21 points) with a good 6-card suit. He opens 1\S.

WEST has an 11-point Limit Raise with four trumps. She jumps to 3\S.

EAST now knows that the partnership holds at least 32 points, perhaps 33. Since he can see that 
the opponents have no way to win the first two tricks he decides to bid the slam, 6\S}

