[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has 14 points and opens 1\S, her 5-card Major.

NORTH could bid 3\S, a Limit Raise with his 11 points. But it is often a good idea, 
when you have five of the Major suit that partner opened with, to just go ahead and bid 
the game. So North should bid 4\S here.

See the NOTE in Deal 13. When you use weaker 5-card support hands for your jump to game, you 
need to find another way to describe your opening-hand-strength type hands.}

